race.comment: VALLO (10) looks to get chance. Has been good in two runs so far, the extra ground suits, this easier and has the claim. Expected to be in the finish. EMPRESS JUPITER (13) has been hard to follow, the latest stepping to a mile and racing on speed but fading in the straight. Drawn much better here bit needs to find best figures. SHREWDNESS (8) stepped up to a mile last time and was beaten a head in a much improved run. Heading the right way and looks well placed here.  SENSATIONAL RULER (6) has been racing in tougher company and will appreciate this level. Fitter for two runs from a spell, the latest effort a sixth over 1800m at Caulfield Heath two weeks ago. This easier and is sure to be thereabouts.
